    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-09-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="33" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 33.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Fish</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                E. B. Washburne</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 164.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-09-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 13, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: A dispatch, dated the 22d ultimo, has been
                            received from Mr. Bancroft, in which he mentions the satisfaction with
                            which your course in regard to the subjects of North Germany is viewed
                            by that government. He incloses a copy of a note upon the subject
                            received by him from the Secretary of State, a translation of which, he
                            informs me, he has sent to to you. I am pleased to assure you that your
                            course has given equal satisfaction to this Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
